quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,217,"And put your trust in the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful,"
  26,218,"Who sees you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) when you stand up (alone at night for Tahajjud prayers)."
  26,219,"And your movements among those who fall prostrate (to Allâh in the five compulsory congregational prayers)."
  33,70,"O you who believe! Keep your duty to Allâh and fear Him, and speak (always) the truth."
  33,71,"He will direct you to do righteous good deeds and will forgive you your sins. And whosoever obeys Allâh and His Messenger (صلى الله عليه وسلم), he has indeed achieved a great achievement (i.e. he will be saved from the Hell-fire and will be admitted to Paradise)."
  33,72,"Truly, We did offer Al-Amânah (the trust or moral responsibility or honesty and all the duties which Allâh has ordained) to the heavens and the earth, and the mountains, but they declined to bear it and were afraid of it (i.e. afraid of Allâh’s Torment). But man bore it. Verily, he was unjust (to himself) and ignorant (of its results).[2]"
  34,49,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  34,50,"Say: "
  34,51,"And if you could but see, when they will be terrified with no escape (for them), and they will be seized from a near place."
  35,34,"And they will say: "
  35,35,"Who, out of His Grace, has lodged us in a home that will last forever, where toil will touch us not nor weariness will touch us."
  35,36,"But those who disbelieve (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism), for them will be the Fire of Hell. Neither will it have a complete killing effect on them so that they die, nor shall its torment be lightened for them. Thus do We requite every disbeliever!"
  36,19,"They (Messengers) said: "
  36,20,"And there came a man running from the farthest part of the town. He said: "
  36,21,""
  37,4,"Verily your Ilâh (God) is indeed One (i.e. Allâh):"
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and of the earth, and all that is between them, and Lord of every point of the sun’s risings.{1}",1:[{37:5} The sun has approx. 365 points for its rising and 365 points for its setting (i.e. the number of days of a solar year). Every day it rises and sets in a new point, till the end of the year, then it comes back to the same point after a year. [See Tafsir Al-Qurtubi,].]
  37,6,"Verily We have adorned the near heaven with the stars (for beauty).{1}",1:[{37:6} See the footnote of {6:97}.]
